<TITLE> Bulbul, Pilot, Rafique to work with academy, age-level teams </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 2 (bdnews24.com)  Former national captains Aminul Islam Bulbul, Khaled Mashud Pilot and left-arm spinner Mohammad Rafique will be seen again in the filed as consultants for the academy and different age-level teams. The BCB Game Development Committee had decided to engage the trio as consultants for the academy, Under-19 and other age-group selections, said a BCB press release Saturday. "This is an effort on our part to make optimum use of local expertise in developing our future cricketers," said Shakil Kasem, the chairman of the game development committee. "Aminul, Mashud and Rafique have vast experience of playing cricket at the highest level and can pass on their knowledge to the next generation," said the former national cricketer. Aminul, Mashud and Rafique, country's highest wicket-taker in Tests, will give their wise expertise in batting, wicket-keeping and spin bowling respectively. The three stalwarts of Bangladesh cricket will work with the cricketers of the GP-BCB national cricket academy, Bangladesh under-19 team and other age-group selections. 
